com.codeferm.dbaccess

Class DbAccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.codeferm.dbaccess.DbAccess
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DbBeanMapper, DbJdbcTemplate, DbPersist, DbQueryRunnerConn, DbQueryRunnerDs

    public abstract class DbAccess
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract class to simplify JDBC database access across all JDBC wrapper implementations. The goal is to have a common database API without coding to a specific implementation such as Apache DBUtils or Spring JdbcTemplate. This allows you to swap out the implementation as needed without impacting dependant code. All implementations support named parameters as well. Transactional support can be added using the Transaction annotation. Implementations should automatically handle database field names with underscores and map them to camelCase bean fields.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    sgoldsmith
    See Also:
    DbBeanMapper, DbJdbcConn, DbJdbcDs, DbJdbcTemplate, DbPersist, DbQueryRunnerConn, DbQueryRunnerDs
